      <caption>
        <p>The Bub3 binding domain of mBub1 and hBubR1 is conserved. BHK cells were transfected with GSTâhBub3 (lanes <italic>1</italic>, <italic>4</italic>, and <italic>5</italic>) and/or Myc-tagged hBubR1 (lanes <italic>2</italic> and <italic>4</italic>), and/or Myc-tagged hBubR1Î42 (lanes <italic>3</italic> and <italic>5</italic>). Proteins from cell lysates (<italic>top</italic>) and purified GSTâ hBub3 complexes (<italic>bottom</italic>) were resolved by SDS-PAGE, transferred to a membrane, and then probed with anti-GST and anti-Myc antibodies. In the absence of GSTâhBub3, neither hBubR1 nor hBubR1Î42 purify with the glutathione beads (lanes <italic>2</italic> and <italic>3</italic>). In the presence of GSTâhBub3, hBubR1 purifies with the glutathione beads (lane <italic>4</italic>) but hBubR1Î42 does not (lane <italic>5</italic>). Note that GST-hBub3 cannot be identified in the cell lysates.</p>
